We had taco edition cater for a small gathering and we are so incredibly happy we did. The food was great and all our guests loved the food, especially the shrimp in the naked shrimp burrito and the tinga tacos. While placing the order, the workers and managers were incredibly kind and helpful, asking us to try the sauces so we could know what we would like. They were also incredibly kind to let us use their crate to transport the food to our nearby building. Highly recommend for either your casual lunch/dinner or your catered events. Thank you guys!

First time ordering from this place because of the good reviews. I ordered the Naked Burrito with chicken which is basically a burrito bowl, and I was quite disappointed. Not much to this $14 dish regarding flavor. Portion size is accurate however, the experience was terribly underwhelming. While it looked appetizing, the chicken specifically was lacking flavor and more importantly SALT. For a dish that has several components of potential flavor (salsa, avocado crema, cheese) everything somehow tasted the same—zero layers of flavor. Not only that but a top the bed of once (Hopefully) freshly grated cheese sat the hot chicken, which just made one large blanket of curdled, terribly textured cheese? Quite sad. Not intending on going back. *Warning* those who have a true respect for food and flavor I advise you not waste you’re time here. Your typical whitewashed version of Mexican food.

This is my first time after they rebranding and second time for this place. When i came in, it was time between shift. So i had a chance to meet both staff. They were really friendly and service minded. For food, It's not like others Mexican food i've tried. Their food is flavourful and rich. I ordered quite a lot of food as my friend and i were starving; lamb taco, pork taco, beef quesadillas extra mushroom, tinga tostadas, tostones, fried sweet plantain and churros. Great job. I like almost all of them. This is my first time to try tostones, not a fan but it's a good combination with dipping sauce. Tostadas seems to be my least favourite. My number one choice still be lamb tacos. But quesadillas is so damn good, will be my next favourite. Highly recommended. Oh! Please be noted that there is no restroom here.

I used to buy here when it was Tacos Project and the tacos were ok.  But I went there last Friday and other than the name, the quality changed as well. I ordered 6 tacos. All of them  were salty, the meat was overcooked, they put more than necessary hot sauce, but we still could notice that the meat was old. They tried to  cover that they were selling  old stuff! I will never go there again. They've lost me as a client. We ordered 2 al pastor 2 tinga 1 biftec and 1 carnitas.

Here tacos take an hour.  I order for pick-up and they give me an estimated time.  Knowing they're slow, I wait an extra 10 minutes before showing up, but then still wait 30-40 minutes when I get to the restaurant.  Good tacos, though.

Good vibes and cozy new spot for tacos and Mexican food lovers in East Williamsburg. The interior is nice. White wood planks colored by multiple flavors of Jarritos bottles on the wall is dope.  The Tacos. I've tried all kind of those but my favorite is Tostadas de camoron. Perfectly fried shrimp, juicy and crunchy on top of smashed avocado and crispy tortilla, garnished with lettuce, roasted coconut, little diced radish. Mind blown. My second is Orejas. I've never had pig ear tacos before and I loved it. Perfectly soft and flavorful boiled pig ears with salsa, garnished with diced radish and cilantro.  5 stars from me😊
